How can I use JSON data to count the number of occurrences of a specific sequence in a DNA string? Suppose I have a DNA string represented in JSON format like this:
{
  "dnaString": "ATCGCGATCGCGATCGCGATCGCGATCG",
  "searchSequence": "ATCG"
}
What code can I write to count the number of times the search sequence appears in the DNA string using JSON data in Python?
